This paper deals with the routing challenges in mobile ad hoc networks, which is a subfield of computer networking (cs.NI). The proposed algorithm uses artificial immune system (AIS) to enhance the efficiency of the OLSR routing protocol, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques (cs.AI). The algorithm also considers hop count and distance among nodes, which are related to graph theory and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the use of AIS involves modeling and control of complex systems, which falls under systems and control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper also discusses the performance metrics such as packet delivery ratio, throughput, end-end delay, and lifetime, which are related to information theory and communication systems (cs.IT).
